<h1>Columbus Reports on His First Voyage, 1493 - Part 3</h1>

<p>The 
  <span class="term">people
    <span class="popup">The inhabitants of Hispaniola encountered by Columbus.</span>
  </span> here are all, as I said before, unprovided with any sort of 
  <span class="term">iron
    <span class="popup">A strong metal used for tools, weapons, and building.</span>
  </span>, and they have barely any 
  <span class="term">guns
    <span class="popup">Weapons using gunpowder to fire projectiles.</span>
  </span>, which are entirely unknown to them, and for which they are not adapted; not on account of any bodily deformity, for they are well made, but because they are 
  <span class="term">timid
    <span class="popup">Easily frightened; lacking courage in the presence of danger.</span>
  </span> and full of 
  <span class="term">terror
    <span class="popup">Extreme fear.</span>
  </span>.
</p>

